Getting started
---------
-Pick a spreadsheet program
Excel/Google Sheets | https://www.google.com/sheets/about/
Basic, yet powerful, spreadsheets, the bread and butter of data reporting

Sources of Data
---------
Data Portals | http://journalismtools.io/tool/dataportals/
A massive listing of open data portals across the world

Open Minneapolis | http://opendata.minneapolismn.gov/
A great source of public city data

American FactFinder | https://factfinder.census.gov/faces/nav/jsf/pages/index.xhtml
The U.S. Census Bureau's impressive lookup tool

Census Explorer | http://www.census.gov/censusexplorer/
Another cool tool from the U.S. Census Bureau

Minnesota Secretary of State | http://www.sos.state.mn.us/elections-voting/election-results
Home of Minnesota election results going back multiple years

Tools
---------
-Charting
Google Charts | https://developers.google.com/chart/
DataWrapper | http://datawrapper.de
Online Charts | http://www.onlinecharttool.com/
Silk | http://silk.co

-Mapping
CARTO | https://carto.com/
A free (with limits) and powerful data mapping service

Mapbox | http://mapbox.com
Another free and powerful, though slightly more complex, data mapping service

QGIS | http://www.qgis.org/en/site/
A more advanced bit of GIS software for building data maps from

-Formatting
Tabula | http://journalismtools.io/tool/tabula/
Turn PDFs into spreadsheets

-More
Tons of data tools
http://journalismtools.io/tools/
http://striblab.github.io/startribune_dataviz/index_browse.html?page=resources

Tips
---------
-Learn some coding
--HTML/CSS
--JS
--Python

-Always ask for spreadsheets

-Be patient